rComments: One of the best prof's I've ever had, enjoys teaching and has a great attitude which is clearly prevalent in every lecture she teaches. I wish she taught more classes!

Very interesting class. Highly recommended for students in the minor as one of the language options. A little less focused on language than the other language classes in Celtic but interesting look at the Celtic culture.  Not very well suited to teaching large classes but good one-on-one. Easy marks with a little effort.

Amazing woman, great teacher, full of stories and knowledge and beautiful songs and was an utter joy to have as a teacher.  Was very aware of how to teach Gaelic to English speakers, and was very helpful. Everyone with the slightest interest in Gaelic should take her course.

a great prof and VERY enthusiastic about her subject. gets a little far into witchcraft and psychics but she sings for you! very easy class and the language isn't that bad to learn. i don't speak french very well but it's pretty similar in some ways. but each language has it's tricky parts. a fun class though
what a gem of lady she is.  so gentle and friendly, a true celt.  it's nice to have a course with someone who's so passionate about something.  i'd recommend her anyone.  Slaìte!

It's great that she gets enthusiastic about Scotland and Gaelic, but she should really simmer down on Glengarry County and witchcraft.  I find it hard to believe that Glengarry is the only important Scot settlement in Canada.
Loved her intro to gaelic course. I just wish they offered the second part this year.
Extremely knowledgeable, but if you skip lectures, you -will- fail.
